---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const lastUpdated = "July 14, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Editorial Policy — PSUCheck"
  description="PSUCheck editorial standards: data sourcing methodology, correction policy, update frequency, and content review practices."
  noIndex={false}
>
  <div class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="badge badge-safe" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">Editorial Standards</div>
        <h1>Editorial Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-body">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="legal-content">

          <p class="about-lead" style="font-size:1.1rem;color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.7;">
            PSUCheck is built by a team of PC hardware engineers and enthusiasts. This policy documents
            how we source data, review content, handle corrections, and maintain editorial independence.
          </p>

          <h2>1. Our Editorial Standards</h2>
          <p>
            PSUCheck is an independent, unbiased website. We do not accept payment from hardware
            manufacturers for product placement, recommendations, or editorial coverage. Our content
            is driven by engineering accuracy and verifiable data, not commercial relationships.
          </p>
          <p>
            All calculator tools, guides, and comparison pages are produced by our team and reviewed
            for technical accuracy against published specifications from manufacturers and independent
            testing laboratories.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Data Sourcing Standards</h2>
          <p>Every specification used in PSUCheck is sourced from published, verifiable references:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>CPU Power Data:</strong> Intel PL2 (Maximum Turbo Power) from Intel ARK. AMD TDP from AMD official specifications.</li>
            <li><strong>GPU Power Data:</strong> Total Board Power (TBP) from NVIDIA/AMD official product pages, cross-referenced with TechPowerUp GPU database.</li>
            <li><strong>Transient Multipliers:</strong> GPU and CPU transient scaling factors from Cybenetics PSU Lab published methodology.</li>
            <li><strong>ATX 3.1 Spec:</strong> Transient tolerance standards from Intel ATX 3.1 Design Guide (2024 revision).</li>
            <li><strong>Efficiency Curves:</strong> 80 PLUS efficiency data from CLEAResult 80 PLUS certification program public records.</li>
            <li><strong>PSU Quality Tiers:</strong> Based on Cultists Network PSU tier list cross-referenced with Cybenetics test results.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            If a data point cannot be sourced from a published reference, it is explicitly labeled
            as "estimated" or "unconfirmed." Leaked or rumored hardware specifications are flagged
            with a warning. See our <a href="/methodology">full methodology</a> for detailed formulas.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Correction Policy</h2>
          <p>
            PSUCheck is committed to accuracy. If you find an error — whether a stale price, incorrect
            specification, or outdated recommendation — we want to correct it promptly:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Data corrections:</strong> Reviewed within 48 hours of submission</li>
            <li><strong>Specification errors:</strong> Corrected and deployed within one business week</li>
            <li><strong>Pricing updates:</strong> Batch-updated on a quarterly schedule</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            To report an error, use our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a> with subject "Data Correction."
            Include the specific page URL, the incorrect information, and your source for the correction.
          </p>

          <h2>4. Update Frequency</h2>
          <p>
            PSUCheck content is updated on the following schedule:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Calculator tools:</strong> Updated continuously as new hardware launches</li>
            <li><strong>Component pricing:</strong> Reviewed and updated quarterly</li>
            <li><strong>Core guides:</strong> Reviewed at least every 6 months</li>
            <li><strong>Specification database:</strong> Updated within 2 weeks of new product launches</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>5. Affiliate & Advertising Disclosure</h2>
          <p>
            PSUCheck participates in affiliate programs (Amazon Associates, Newegg Affiliate Program)
            and displays ads via Google AdSense. These relationships do not influence our calculator
            results, recommendations, or editorial content. See our <a href="/disclaimer">full Disclaimer</a>
            and <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> for details.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Independence & Impartiality</h2>
          <p>
            PSUCheck is not affiliated with any hardware manufacturer, retailer, or component brand.
            Unlike manufacturer calculators that recommend only their own products, PSUCheck
            recommends the best PSU for your build regardless of brand. Our recommendation algorithm
            is based on technical specifications, value scoring, and compatibility — not commercial
            relationships.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about this editorial policy, please use our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
.legal-hero {
  padding: 4rem 0 2rem;
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-deep) 0%, var(--bg-primary) 100%);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
}
.legal-meta {
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
}
.legal-body {
  padding: 3rem 0 5rem;
}
.legal-content {
  max-width: 760px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1.5rem;
}
.legal-content h2 {
  font-size: 1.375rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
  padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
}
.legal-content p {
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.75;
  max-width: 70ch;
}
.legal-content ul {
  padding-left: 1.5rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.4rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.6;
}
.about-lead {
  max-width: 70ch;
}
</style>
